<li>Welch Everman, <i>Cult Science Fiction Films</i>, Citadel Press, <a href="/wiki/1995_in_literature" title="1995 in literature">1995</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/080651602X" class="internal">ISBN 0-8065-1602-X</a>.</li>
<li>Peter Guttmacher, <i>Legendary Sci-Fi Movies</i>, <a href="/wiki/1997_in_literature" title="1997 in literature">1997</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1567994903" class="internal">ISBN 1-56799-490-3</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Phil_Hardy_(journalist)" title="Phil Hardy (journalist)">Phil Hardy</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Aurum_Film_Encyclopedia" title="The Aurum Film Encyclopedia">The Overlook Film Encyclopedia, Science Fiction</a></i>. William Morrow and Company, New York, <a href="/wiki/1995_in_literature" title="1995 in literature">1995</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0879516267" class="internal">ISBN 0-87951-626-7</a>.</li>
<li>Richard S. Myers, <i>S-F 2: A pictorial history of science fiction from 1975 to the present</i>, <a href="/wiki/1984_in_literature" title="1984 in literature">1984</a>, Citadel Press, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0806508752" class="internal">ISBN 0-8065-0875-2</a>.</li>
<li>Gregg Rickman, <i>The Science Fiction Film Reader</i>, <a href="/wiki/2004_in_literature" title="2004 in literature">2004</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0879109947" class="internal">ISBN 0-87910-994-7</a>.</li>
<li>Errol Vieth, <i>Screening Science: Context, Text and Science in Fifties Science Fiction Film</i>, Lanham, MD and London: Scarecrow Press, 2001. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0810840235" class="internal">ISBN 0-8108-4023-5</a></li>
</ul>
